The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for vehicle detection in aerial images and videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) domains. The use of a rotatable region proposal network and rotatable detection network involves complex geometric transformations, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper also mentions experiments on aerial videos, indicating the potential involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
